---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  page="home"
  title="Clueless Creations® — A business that runs businesses."
  description="A portfolio holding company running six businesses through an agent harness. Humans on the board; the harness on the floor."
>
  <!-- HERO — atmospheric image / video, single Primary CTA -->
  <section class="hero">
    <picture>
      <img
        src="/hero/hero-poster.avif"
        alt=""
        loading="eager"
        fetchpriority="high"
        width="1920"
        height="1080"
        class="video-bg"
      />
    </picture>
    <video
      class="video-bg"
      autoplay
      loop
      muted
      playsinline
      preload="none"
      poster="/hero/hero-poster.avif"
      aria-hidden="true"
    >
      <source src="/hero/hero.webm" type="video/webm" />
      <source src="/hero/hero.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
    </video>
    <div class="vignette" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="hero-content container-wide">
      <div class="hero-top">
        <div class="animate-fade-rise eyebrow hero-eyebrow">
          <span class="status-dot pulse-dot"></span>
          A portfolio of agent-run businesses
        </div>
        <h1 class="display animate-fade-rise hero-h1">
          A business that <span class="muted">runs</span> other <span class="muted">businesses.</span>
        </h1>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-bottom">
        <p class="animate-fade-rise-delay subheading muted hero-lede">
          Agents discover, validate, build, launch, and operate a portfolio of products.
          Humans sit above as a board of directors — intervening only when judgment is required.
        </p>
        <div class="animate-fade-rise-delay-2 hero-ctas">
          <a href="/about" class="btn-primary">How the harness works →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <style>
      .hero {
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
        height: 100vh;
        min-height: 720px;
      }
      .hero-content {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        z-index: 10;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        padding-top: 6rem;
        padding-bottom: 4rem;
      }
      .hero-top {
        text-align: left;
        max-width: 42rem;
      }
      .hero-bottom {
        margin-top: auto;
        text-align: left;
        max-width: 42rem;
      }
      .hero-eyebrow { margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
      .hero-h1 {
        font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4.0625rem);
        text-shadow:
          0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.85),
          0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.65);
      }
      .hero-eyebrow {
        text-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.85);
      }
      .hero-lede {
        max-width: 36rem;
        margin: 0 0 var(--space-8);
        text-shadow:
          0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.85),
          0 2px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
      }
      .hero-ctas {
        display: flex;
        gap: var(--space-3);
        flex-wrap: wrap;
      }

      /* Desktop: centered eyebrow + H1 at top, CTA bottom-left */
      @media (min-width: 960px) {
        .hero-top {
          text-align: center;
          max-width: none;
          margin: 0 auto;
          width: 100%;
        }
        .hero-top .hero-eyebrow {
          justify-content: center;
          display: inline-flex;
          align-items: center;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </section>

  <!-- THE PREMISE -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-wide premise-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow">01 — The premise</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="heading-lg" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-8);">
          We run businesses with agents, <span class="muted">and we sell the tools and lessons that come from doing it.</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="subheading muted" style="max-width: 48rem;">
          Four streams feed each other. Running businesses generates lessons that become content.
          Building skills generates tools that become products. Products generate usage that
          sharpens skills. Every motion is leveraged.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-wide premise-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow">02 — The model</div>
        <h2 class="heading" style="margin-top: var(--space-4);">Board, not management.</h2>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="subheading muted" style="max-width: 48rem; margin: 0 0 var(--space-8);">
          The harness runs the businesses. The board views through Notion and reports, intervening only at human gates or when the system itself needs improving. When things fail, we fix the harness — not the business. Every failure makes the factory smarter.
        </p>
        <a href="/about" class="btn-primary">Read the full operating model →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CONTACT CTA -->
  <section class="section" style="text-align: center;">
    <div class="container-wide" style="max-width: 48rem; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">03 — Reach the board</div>
      <h2 class="display" style="margin: 0 auto var(--space-10); max-width: 18ch;">
        <span class="muted">Operators,</span> investors, <span class="muted">fellow travelers.</span>
      </h2>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Get in touch</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .premise-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-10);
    }
    @media (min-width: 768px) {
      .premise-grid {
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(0, 2fr);
        gap: var(--space-14);
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
